{
  "id": "c0c0c0c0-005a-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "name": "Auto-Generated Diagrams",
  "type": "871ae771-b9b1-4f40-8c7f-d9038bfb69c3",
  "created": 1741219200000,
  "modified": 1775756671680,
  "content": {
    "description": [
      ":doc",
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Idea: generate SVG diagrams from item data, rendered via functional transclusion or custom views. No new storage needed — diagrams are computed live from existing item metadata."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Motivation"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Hobson's reactive wiring (events, watches, dependencies) is spread across many items and two mechanisms (declarative watches + programmatic "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "events.on()"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": "). No single place shows the full picture. Auto-generated diagrams would make system structure visible at a glance."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Diagram Types (by priority)"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "1. Event Flow Diagram"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Visualize the full emit-subscribe wiring: which items emit which events, which items subscribe (with filter conditions), and how events flow through the system."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Data sources:"
          }
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Declarative: "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "content.watches"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " arrays (machine-readable, ~15 items)"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Programmatic: "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "events.on()"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " and "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "events.emit()"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " calls in "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "content.code"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " (~6 items)"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            {
              "s": "Event type hierarchy: "
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "e0e00000-*"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " items define the event tree"
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Why useful:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " The reactive system is invisible without reading every item. Filter conditions ("
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "type"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "typeExtends"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "id"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ") on watches add specificity that's easy to miss. The full wiring spans ~20 items and two mechanisms."
        }
      ],
      [
        "do",
        [
          "transclusion-chrome",
          [
            "call-export",
            "@d1a00000-0001-0000-0000-000000000000",
            {
              "s": "eventFlow"
            },
            "api"
          ],
          ":source",
          "@d1a00000-0001-0000-0000-000000000000",
          ":symbol",
          {
            "s": "eventFlow"
          }
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "2. Code Dependency Graph"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Visualize "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "api.require()"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " relationships between code items. ~63 items have dependencies."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Natural clusters:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " editor cluster (field-view-"
        },
        [
          ":em",
          {
            "s": " -> codemirror), Hob cluster (hob-"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": "-tests -> hob-interpreter), view boilerplate ("
        },
        [
          ":em",
          {
            "s": "-view-"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " -> generic-view), system cluster (keyboard-shortcuts -> context-menu-lib -> item-search-lib)."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Hub libraries:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " generic-view (10 dependents), test-lib (14), hob-interpreter (12), item-search-lib (7), modal-lib (7)."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        [
          ":strong",
          {
            "s": "Why useful:"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " \"What breaks if I change this library?\" Reverse dependency lookup. Cluster identification. The data is non-obvious without reading every code item."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "3. Item Relationship Graph (proof of concept)"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Generic visualization of attachments, tags, type chains, and "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "item://"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " references for a given item. Pretty but often not useful in practice — the spatial canvas and tag browser already show most of this."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Implementation Approach"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Phase 1: Declarative event flow (proof of concept) (IMPLEMENTED)"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "A "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "diagram-lib"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " library item that generates inline SVG. Consume via functional transclusion: "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "![](item://diagram-lib?call=eventFlow)"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ". Reads only declarative "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "content.watches"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " — no code analysis needed."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "!"
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "d1a00000-0001-0000-0000-000000000000?call=eventFlow"
          }
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Phase 2: Extend symbol extractor for "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "_deps"
          }
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Add a "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "content._deps"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " field alongside "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "content._symbols"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", auto-generated by the existing "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "ac0ac0ac-0004-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "symbol-indexer-watch"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " infrastructure:"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":code-block",
        {
          "s": "\"_deps\": {\n  \"requires\": [\"generic-view\", \"modal-lib\"],\n  \"subscribes\": [{ \"event\": \"ITEM_UPDATED\", \"raw\": \"EVENT_IDS.ITEM_UPDATED\" }],\n  \"emits\": [{ \"event\": \"SELECTION_CHANGED\" }]\n}"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "The Acorn AST already has "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "CallExpression"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " nodes — add cases for "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "*.require(StringLiteral)"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "*.events.on(...)"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ", "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "*.events.emit(...)"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": ". The "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "ac0ac0ac-0003-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "symbol-extractor-lib"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " currently only captures definition sites, not call sites, but the walker infrastructure handles it."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Challenge: resolving "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "EVENT_IDS.ITEM_UPDATED"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " constants to actual event GUIDs requires knowledge of the EVENT_IDS map from "
        },
        [
          ":item-ref",
          {
            "s": "33333333-1111-0000-0000-000000000000"
          },
          {
            "s": "kernel:core"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": "."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h3",
        {
          "s": "Phase 3: Full diagrams"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "With "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "_deps"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " on every code item, both the event flow and dependency graph become trivial queries over item metadata. Add layout algorithms, interactivity (click to navigate), and cluster detection."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "Design Considerations"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "SVG over Canvas"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — SVG is text, renders natively in DOM, works with transclusion, no binary storage needed"
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Live vs static"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — Functional transclusion re-executes on render, so diagrams auto-update. But scanning all items is O(n). Consider caching or limiting scope."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Interactivity"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — SVG elements can have click handlers for navigation ("
            },
            [
              ":code",
              {
                "s": "api.navigate()"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": "). Hovering could show item details."
            }
          ]
        ],
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
            [
              ":strong",
              {
                "s": "Layout"
              }
            ],
            {
              "s": " — Force-directed for relationship graphs, layered/hierarchical for event flow and dependency DAGs. Could use a simple custom layout or a library like dagre (if added as an item)."
            }
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "See Also"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":ul",
        [
          ":li",
          [
            ":p",
